SIMPLE: overcharge
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Overcharge
<hw>O`ver*charge"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Supercharge</er>, <er>Surcharge</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To charge or load too heavily; to burden; to
oppress; to cloy.</def> <rj><au>Sir W. Raleigh.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To fill too full; to crowd.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Our language is <qex>overcharged</qex> with consonants.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To charge (a buyer) an excessive price; to charge
beyond a fair rate or price.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To exaggerate; <as>as, to <ex>overcharge</ex> a
description</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <fld>(Electricity)</fld> <def>To charge (a battery) too
much, so as to cause damage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Overcharged mine</b></col>. <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <cd>See
<cref>Globe of compression</cref>, under <er>Globe</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overcharge</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Overcharge
<hw>O`ver*charge"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To make excessive
charges.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overcharge</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Overcharge
<hw>O"ver*charge`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Supercargo</er>, <er>Supercharge</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>An excessive load or burden.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An excessive charge in an account.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overclimb</ent>⟦br⟧
